# __APPA_PROJECT_NAME__

An Appa instance. Generic chat-with-tutor-plus-team-workspace, customized for this project.

## Prerequisites

- **Node.js 20+** (`node --version` to check)
- **Claude Code CLI** on your `$PATH` (`claude --version` should print something — install from https://docs.claude.com/claude-code/getting-started)
- **Anthropic API key** from https://console.anthropic.com/ — each chat round costs real money against this key. A class of 25 × full day can run a few dollars; switch to `model: "haiku"` in `appa.config.js` for high-volume use.

## Run

```bash
cp .env.example .env  # then edit and set ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
npm install
npm start
```

Then open <http://127.0.0.1:3848>. Pick a member from the dropdown, start chatting.

> **⚠️ Auth warning.** The dev-mode picker uses `devAuth()`, which trusts whatever id the client claims. Anyone who can reach this URL can act as any member — including the coach. Do not expose this server to the open internet without putting a real auth layer in front of it (Tailscale Funnel device-auth, a reverse proxy with SSO, signed cookies, etc.). See the `resolveCaller` field in `appa.config.js`.

## Files

- `appa.config.js` — which modules to load and runtime settings; **also where you wire real auth**
- `team.json` — your roster (coaches + members; `groupId` for class sections)
- `tutor-prompt.md` — the tutor persona. The opening line is the LLM's mission — replace it with your project's specific goal in one sentence
- `shared-memory.md` — knowledge the tutor sees in every session. Grows automatically as sessions end and the kernel summarizes; seed it by hand with project context (hard facts, vocabulary, decisions). **Editing this file affects every user's tutor**, so coach-only context here will be visible to students
- `.env.example` — copy to `.env` and fill in the API key

Data files are created lazily as modules are used (`tasks.json`, `photos.json`, `transcripts/`, `.threads.json`, etc.).

`transcripts/` is gitignored by default for student-privacy reasons. If you want git-based backup of chat history, remove that line from `.gitignore` — but then be careful about who can read the repo.

## Adding a module

Create `modules/my-module.js` exporting an [AppaModule](https://github.com/karl-kahn/appa#modules), then import it in `appa.config.js`:

```js
import myModule from "./modules/my-module.js";
// ...
export default defineConfig({
  modules: [tasks, photos, activity, myModule],
});
```
